<br>
I dont really know where you'd find strategies and all for PoA.  Ummmm, Everlore might have some but it's mostly wanna be's making things up or asking what drops there.  The thing is that not to many people go there so frankly its hard to find guides out there on it.  <br>
<br>
PoA really isnt that bad.  The mobs are as easy and hard as any other out there.  Mostly on the Kunark model at the hardest, there arent really Velious type uncharmable, unmezable, unsnareable/rootable mobs there.  Killing them is much the same as anywhere else.  Set up camp on an island, send monk sacrafice out, monk brings back a pull or two, group slaughters them or gets slaughtered.  The only tricky part is CR, but as long as you have a cleric camped its not too hard.  I apologize if I gave the impression PoA is some massively hard and difficult zone.  It really is no harder or easier than any other 46+ zone out there.  However, some things dont work and I want people to be prepared.  <br>
<br>
The major hard part is the expense (400-600pp a person) and the time commitment.  Once you are there, your there.  There's no quick rez runs in WC, no quick reagent pickups in EC, no I have to go to a family picnic I'll be back in 5 hours.  Either you can be there uninterrupted for the 3 days, or you cant be and dont go.  Thats something thats very hard for a group like CoG to pull off.  Personally I wouldnt even by trying if Zellex hadnt asked for it.  *shrug*  I suppose its worth a try.<br>
<br>
